trans-unit.source: Used to group collections of controls.
trans-unit.target: Brukes til gruppen samlinger av kontroller.

trans-unit.source: A Panel is a control that contains other controls.
trans-unit.target: Et Panel er en kontroll som inneholder andre kontroller.

trans-unit.source: You can use a Panel to group collections of controls such as a group of <xref:System.Windows.Forms.RadioButton> controls.
trans-unit.target: Du kan bruke en panelet til gruppen samlinger av kontroller for eksempel en gruppe <xref:System.Windows.Forms.RadioButton>Kontroller.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.RadioButton>

trans-unit.source: As with other container controls such as the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.GroupBox> control, if the Panel control's <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Enabled%2A> property is set to `false`, the controls contained within the Panel will also be disabled.
trans-unit.target: Som med andre kontroller beholder som den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.GroupBox>kontrollerer om panelet kontrollens <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Enabled%2A>er satt til `false`, deaktiveres også kontroller innenfor panelet.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Enabled%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.GroupBox>

trans-unit.source: The Panel control is displayed by default without any borders.
trans-unit.target: Panelet kontrollen skal vises som standard uten kantlinjer.

trans-unit.source: You can provide a standard or three-dimensional border using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Panel.BorderStyle%2A> property to distinguish the area of the panel from other areas on the form.
trans-unit.target: Du kan angi en standard eller tredimensjonale kantlinje ved hjelp av <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Panel.BorderStyle%2A>til å skille området for panelet fra andre områder i skjemaet.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.Panel.BorderStyle%2A>

trans-unit.source: Because the Panel control derives from the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ScrollableControl> class, you can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ScrollableControl.AutoScroll%2A> property to enable scroll bars in the Panel control.
trans-unit.target: Fordi panelet kontrollen er avledet fra den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ScrollableControl>klasse, kan du bruke den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ScrollableControl.AutoScroll%2A>til å aktivere side-felt i panelet-kontroll.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.ScrollableControl.AutoScroll%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.ScrollableControl>

trans-unit.source: When the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ScrollableControl.AutoScroll%2A> property is set to `true`, any controls located within the Panel (but outside of its visible region), can be scrolled to with the scroll bars provided.
trans-unit.target: Når den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ScrollableControl.AutoScroll%2A>er satt til `true`, eventuelle kontroller i panelet (men utenfor området som er synlige), kan rulles med det angitte rullefeltet.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.ScrollableControl.AutoScroll%2A>

trans-unit.source: The Panel control does not display a caption.
trans-unit.target: Panelet kontrollen Vis ikke en tittel.

trans-unit.source: If you need a control similar to a Panel that can display a caption, see the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.GroupBox> control.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du trenger en kontroll ligner en panelet som kan vise en tekst, kan du se den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.GroupBox>kontroll.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.GroupBox>

trans-unit.source: Fires the event indicating that the panel has been resized.
trans-unit.target: Starter hendelsen som angir at panelet er endret.

trans-unit.source: Inheriting controls should use this in favor of actually listening to the event, but should still call <xref uid="langword_csharp_base.onResize" name="base.onResize" href=""></xref> to ensure that the event is fired for external listeners.
trans-unit.target: Arving Kontroller bør bruke dette til fordel faktisk lytter til hendelsen, men fortsatt må kalle <xref uid="langword_csharp_base.onResize" name="base.onResize" href=""> </xref> å sikre at hendelsen starter for eksterne lyttere.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets a value indicating whether the user can give the focus to this control using the TAB key.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir en verdi som angir om brukeren kan gi fokus til kontrollen bruker du TAB.

trans-unit.source: When the user presses the TAB key, the input focus is set to the next control in the tab order.
trans-unit.target: Når du trykker du TAB, er inndata fokus satt til den neste kontrollen i kategorien rekkefølge.

trans-unit.source: Controls with the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.TabStop%2A> property value of `false` are not included in the collection of controls in the tab order.
trans-unit.target: Kontrollerer med den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.TabStop%2A>egenskapsverdi for `false` inkluderes ikke i samlingen av kontroller i kategorien rekkefølge.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.TabStop%2A>

trans-unit.source: The tab order can be manipulated by setting the control's <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.TabIndex%2A> property value.
trans-unit.target: Kategorirekkefølgen kan endres ved å angi kontrollens <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.TabIndex%2A>egenskapsverdi.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.TabIndex%2A>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > The TabStop property has no effect on the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Panel> control as it is a container object.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > For TabStop egenskapen har ingen innvirkning på den <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Panel>kontrollere som det er en container-objekt.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.Panel>

trans-unit.source: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the user can give the focus to the control using the TAB key; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>Hvis brukeren kan gi fokus til kontrollen bruker du TAB; Ellers <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>.
